Carrie Mathison, a CIA operations officer, is on probation after carrying out an unauthorized operation in Iraq. As a result, 
she has been reassigned to the Counter terrorism center.

When Nicholas Brody, a U.S. Marine Sergeant, is rescued after being held hostage since 2003, 
she suspects that he is the turned American prisoner. 
Brody is received home as a war hero, so Carrie goes to any lengths possible, ignoring protocol, to catch him out.
